==English==
===Noun===
'''Zugzwang''' (also '''zugzwang''')
*(chess) A position in which one player is put at a disadvantage because he/she has to make a move.

==German==

===Etymology===
Composite German word, meaning "compulsion to move".

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Zugzwang'''
# A situation where somebody is forced to act, but would prefer to remain passive. This is most common when a politician does not want to touch some controversial issue, but his/her political opponents work to create a situation where he/she must act.
# In chess, zugzwang occurs when one player is put at a disadvantage because he/she has to make a move.